                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/610: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Puerto Cortes</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fox</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-10T11:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1928—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. For Minister Davis: Your 1, April 5, 6 p.m. The Department’s telegram No. 8,
                    of March 23, 6 p.m. modifies its mail instruction No. 1, which was dispatched
                    before the receipt of the authorization by the two Governments for you to fix
                    the provisional line in the event the commissioners are unable to agree.</p>
                <p>The Department would view with favor the definitive arbitration of the dispute by
                    the International Central American Tribunal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
